FIG. 1 is a vector diagram showing the relative intensities of interfering light in a flying height tester;


FIG. 2 is a schematic of an embodiment of an apparatus of the present invention;


FIG. 3 is a bottom view of a double image on a photodetector;


FIG. 4 is a graph showing a correlation between a phase value and a flying height;


FIG. 5 is a graph showing a correlation between a normalized modulation amplitude and the flying height.

0 (slashed zero) =a measured phase value;


h=the flying height;


Rg =the reflectance of the glass-air interface, which can be predetermined;


Rs =the reflectance of the air-slider interface which is defined by the equation (n-1)/(n+1) and can be computed or predetermined, n being the real index of refraction of the slider;


LAMBDA =the wavelength of the reflected light.
